y of descriptiveness under Article 7(1)(c)","why_it_matters_en":"Names of famous figures face heightened refusal risks for books, films, and educational services where the name signals content topic"},{"rank":4,"sequence_label_zh":"第四","sequence_label_en":"Fourth","item_id":11476,"source_name":"Mondaq","ip_type":"patent","ip_type_label_zh":"专利","ip_type_label_en":"Patents","title_zh":"统一专利法院上诉庭准许口头听证使用英语的裁定","title_en":"UPC Court of Appeal Permits English Oral Pleadings Despite French Language of Proceedings","title":"CoA, May 15, 2026, Order On Request For Use Of English At Oral Hearing, UPC-CoA-50/2026","published_at":"2026-05-26 00:00:00","url":"https://www.mondaq.com/germany/patent/1792274/coa-may-15-2026-order-on-request-for-use-of-english-at-oral-hearing-upc-coa-502026","what_happened_zh":"法院基于程序规则前言的灵活性原则，准许在非程序语言的口头听证中使用英语","why_it_matters_zh":"程序语言与庭审口语可分离，需证明语言能力不足及对方同意","what_happened_en":"The Court permitted English oral pleadings while retaining French as the formal language of proceedings based on pragmat...","why_it_matters_en":"Parties facing language proficiency gaps can seek oral hearing adjustments without formally changing the case language, provided opposi..."}],"opening_line_zh":"今天是2026年5月26日。以下是今天欧洲 IP 圈最重要的几条变化。","opening_line_en":"Today is May 26, 2026. Here are the most relevant European IP developments in today's briefing.","closing_line_zh":"总结来看，今天的欧洲 IP 动态仍然围绕专利、商标展开，接下来值得继续关注CRISPR-Cas9专利阵营在欧洲的最新诉讼动态。","closing_line_en":"Overall, today's European IP signals center on Patents, Trade marks, General IP. The next point to watch is Further court orders, institutional guidance and specialist commentary on the same issues.","transcript_lines_zh":["今天是2026年5月26日。以下是今天欧洲 IP 圈最重要的几条变化。","先看第一条，DPMA为配合2026年世界杯，更新了展示全球足球相关专利的在线画廊。后续要看德国会不会围绕这类官方动向继续给出配套安排或更明确口径。","再看第二条，异议须向欧洲专利局书面或电子提交，并在提交时缴纳官方费用。后续要看欧洲层面会不会围绕这类官方动向继续给出配套安排或更明确口径。","再看第三条，EUIPO大上诉委员会拒绝“GEORGE ORWELL”在书籍及娱乐服务上的欧盟商标注册。值得关注的是，名人姓名在书籍、影音等内容类产品上易被认定为描述性标志。","最后看第四条，法院基于程序规则前言的灵活性原则，准许在非程序语言的口头听证中使用英语。值得关注的是，程序语言与庭审口语可分离，需证明语言能力不足及对方同意。","总结来看，今天的欧洲 IP 动态仍然围绕专利、商标展开，接下来值得继续关注CRISPR-Cas9专利阵营在欧洲的最新诉讼动态。"],"transcript_lines_en":["Today is May 26, 2026. Here are the most relevant European IP developments in today's briefing.","First, DPMA updates its online gallery with recent patents including AI-driven safety nets and robotics. Why it matters: Demonstrates the DPMA's strategic emphasis on IP as a tool for commercializing sports-related innovations and protecting R&D investment.","Next, Opposition notices must be filed in writing or electronically with the official fee paid at submission. Why it matters: Understanding the narrow scope of allowable opposition grounds helps rights holders assess the viability of challenging competitor pate.","Next, Grand Board confirms subject matter is a recognized subcategory of descriptiveness under Article 7(1)(c). Why it matters: Names of famous figures face heightened refusal risks for books, films, and educational services where the name signals content topic.","Finally, The Court permitted English oral pleadings while retaining French as the formal language of proceedings based on pragmat. Why it matters: Parties facing language proficiency gaps can seek oral hearing adjustments without formally changing the case language, provided opposi.","Overall, today's European IP signals center on Patents, Trade marks, General IP. The next point to watch is Further court orders, institutional guidance and specialist commentary on the same issues."],"transcript_zh":"今天是2026年5月26日。以下是今天欧洲 IP 圈最重要的几条变化。\n先看第一条，DPMA为配合2026年世界杯，更新了展示全球足球相关专利的在线画廊。后续要看德国会不会围绕这类官方动向继续给出配套安排或更明确口径。\n再看第二条，异议须向欧洲专利局书面或电子提交，并在提交时缴纳官方费用。后续要看欧洲层面会不会围绕这类官方动向继续给出配套安排或更明确口径。\n再看第三条，EUIPO大上诉委员会拒绝“GEORGE ORWELL”在书籍及娱乐服务上的欧盟商标注册。值得关注的是，名人姓名在书籍、影音等内容类产品上易被认定为描述性标志。\n最后看第四条，法院基于程序规则前言的灵活性原则，准许在非程序语言的口头听证中使用英语。值得关注的是，程序语言与庭审口语可分离，需证明语言能力不足及对方同意。\n总结来看，今天的欧洲 IP 动态仍然围绕专利、商标展开，接下来值得继续关注CRISPR-Cas9专利阵营在欧洲的最新诉讼动态。","transcript_en":"Today is May 26, 2026. Here are the most relevant European IP developments in today's briefing.\nFirst, DPMA updates its online gallery with recent patents including AI-driven safety nets and robotics. Why it matters: Demonstrates the DPMA's strategic emphasis on IP as a tool for commercializing sports-related innovations and protecting R&D investment.\nNext, Opposition notices must be filed in writing or electronically with the official fee paid at submission. Why it matters: Understanding the narrow scope of allowable opposition grounds helps rights holders assess the viability of challenging competitor pate.\nNext, Grand Board confirms subject matter is a recognized subcategory of descriptiveness under Article 7(1)(c). Why it matters: Names of famous figures face heightened refusal risks for books, films, and educational services where the name signals content topic.\nFinally, The Court permitted English oral pleadings while retaining French as the formal language of proceedings based on pragmat. Why it matters: Parties facing language proficiency gaps can seek oral hearing adjustments without formally changing the case language, provided opposi.\nOverall, today's European IP signals center on Patents, Trade marks, General IP. The next point to watch is Further court orders, institutional guidance and specialist commentary on the same issues.","estimated_duration_seconds":105,"estimated_duration_seconds_en":82,"target_duration_seconds":90,"max_duration_seconds":120,"item_ids":[11458,11481,11478,11476],"voice_provider":"edge_tts","voice_name":"zh-CN-YunjianNeural","voice_model":"Microsoft Edge Neural TTS","voice_provider_en":"edge_tts","voice_name_en":"en-US-GuyNeural","voice_model_en":"Microsoft Edge Neural TTS","audio_path":"storage/audio-briefs/2026/05/26/20260526-190827-brief.mp3","audio_path_en":"storage/audio-briefs/2026/05/26/20260526-190827-brief-en.mp3","audio_url":"eu_ip_sentinel_assets/data/audio-briefs/daily-latest.20260526-201600.mp3","audio_url_en":"eu_ip_sentinel_assets/data/a